  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "design manager",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Coordinate with clients, consultants, subcontractors, and internal teams on design matters.</p></li><li><p>Manage design drawings, specifications, samples, and submissions.</p></li><li><p>Review architectural and MEP drawings to ensure buildability and technical alignment.</p></li><li><p>Identify and resolve design discrepancies, clashes, and technical issues.</p></li><li><p>Assist with authority submissions, approvals, and compliance requirements where necessary.</p></li><li><p>Support tender and pricing teams on design clarifications and material specifications.</p></li><li><p>Ensure timely delivery of design information according to project schedules.</p></li><li><p>Maintain documentation including drawing registers, submission logs, and revision tracking.</p></li><li><p>Participate in meetings and presentations relating to design coordination and material selection.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Degree/Diploma in Architecture, Interior Design, Engineering, or related field.</p></li><li><p>5–10 years of relevant experience in design coordination or project design management.</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of construction drawings, detailing, materials, and fit-out methods.</p></li><li><p>Ability to coordinate across multiple disciplines (Architectural, Structural, MEP).</p></li><li><p>Good understanding of project workflows from design to construction.</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and coordination skills.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with authority codes and submission processes is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>BIM/Revit knowledge is beneficial but not mandatory.</p></li></ul>",
